# UI & Design System Rules
- ALWAYS check `frontend/src/components/ui` before creating any UI element.
- NEVER use raw HTML tags like `<button>`, `<input>`, or `<a>` for primary UI elements.
- ALWAYS use our custom Design System components: `Button`, `Input`, `Card`, `Badge`, `Modal`, etc.
- If a component is missing a variant, extend the existing component instead of creating a new one.
- Use Tailwind CSS with our specific design tokens (Indigo primary, Slate for borders/text).
- All new UI should support Dark Mode by default using Tailwind's `dark:` classes.

# Technical Preferences
- Use `@/components/ui/...` for imports (assuming path aliases are set).
- Maintain consistent spacing and padding following our existing layout.